Deputy President William Ruto has congratulated Ghanaians for conducting free and fair elections.Ruto, who represented President Uhuru Kenyatta, at the swearing-in ceremony of Nana Akufo-Addo as Ghana&rsquo;s new President on Saturday, reaffirmed commitment to deepening ties between Kenya and Ghana. &ldquo;Congratulations to the people of Ghana for conducting a democratic election and a peaceful transition of power. Ghanaians demonstrated political maturity before and after the elections,&rdquo; he said.He said Kenya and Ghana will pursue opportunities in agriculture, energy and trade. The DP said outgoing President John Mahama has shown statesmanship and put Ghana first by conceding defeat and relinquishing power to Akufo-Addo. Liberian President Ellen Johnson Sirleaf, the chairperson of the Economic Community of West African States, said Ghanaians had charted a new destiny. &ldquo;Thank you, the people of Ghana, for showing political maturity and patriotism. You have come together after a hard-fought election and demonstrated togetherness,&rdquo; she said.